# Design Consistency Rule

## Must read first
- Always read `docs/brand-style-guide.md` before editing UI/copy.

## Visual constraints
- Reuse existing CSS variables in `src/app/globals.css`.
- Do not introduce new color tokens unless user explicitly asks.
- Keep typography pairing: heading serif, body sans.
- Prefer whitespace and text hierarchy over heavy cards/borders.

## Interaction constraints
- Keep motion subtle and purposeful.
- Preserve reduced-motion behavior.
- Keep primary CTA prominence (`terracotta`), secondary CTA subdued.

## Content constraints
- Keep bilingual nav format (`English / 日本語`).
- Maintain brand tone: warm, editorial, trustworthy, not flashy.
- Avoid overclaiming; keep copy specific and honest.

## Structural constraints
- Company page must keep legal links (`/tokusho`, `/privacy-policy`).
- Contact page keeps email-first policy and LINE as secondary channel.
- Home page remains fixed hero style unless user explicitly requests change.

## Before finishing
- Verify responsive layout on mobile assumptions.
- Check lints on touched files.
- Report how the change preserved consistency in 3 bullets.
